@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: Authenticated User Reset Password (Secure Flow)

actor User
participant "Frontend/UI" as UI
participant "Backend/API" as API
participant "Auth Middleware (JWT)" as AUTH
participant "Rate Limiter" as RL
database "Database (Neon)" as DB

User -> UI: Open 'Reset password' page

User -> UI: Enter old + new password
UI -> API: POST /auth/reset-password (JWT)

API -> AUTH: Verify JWT
AUTH --> API: Valid / Invalid

alt Invalid Token
    API --> UI: 401 Unauthorized
else Valid
    API -> RL: Check rate limit
    RL --> API: Allowed / Blocked

    alt Rate Limited
        API --> UI: 429 Too Many Requests
    else Allowed
        API -> DB: Fetch user by ID
        DB --> API: Return user record

        API -> API: Compare old password (bcrypt.compare)

        alt Old Password Invalid
            API --> UI: 401 Invalid credentials
        else Valid
            API -> API: Hash new password (bcrypt)
            API -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
            API -> DB: Update password hash
            API -> DB: Delete/Invalidate refresh tokens
            API -> DB: COMMIT
            API --> UI: 200 Password updated
            UI -> UI: Clear local tokens
            UI --> User: Redirect to login page
        end
    end
end


@enduml